=== 7.4 The Code: Multi-Head Attention in Python

Each attention head is a triple of weight matrices stem:[(W_q, W_k, W_v)], each of shape stem:[[d \times d_k\]].

[source,python]
----
include::../../../src/python/microgpt.py[tag=mha]
----

`hstack` concatenates a list of matrices column-wise into a single stem:[[T \times d\]] matrix.

[source,python]
----
include::../../../src/python/microgpt.py[tag=mha]
----

`multi-head-attention` maps over the list of heads, computes SDPA for each independently, hstacks them, and applies the output projection.

[source,python]
----
include::../../../src/python/chapter_demos.py[tag=chapter_07]
----

Run with `python3 src/python/chapter_demos.py`.
